cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with the detection of sclerotic metastases in CT images using a deep Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) classifier. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically a deep CNN, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of a two-tiered cascade framework, which involves the generation of candidate regions of interest (ROI) and the use of random views to train the CNN classifier. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques, which suggests that it may belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
